message.content: cs.PL, cs.MS, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.ET - The paper discusses the use of functional programming in teaching mathematics, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). It also involves the creation of domain-specific languages (DSLs) for mathematics, which could be classified under mathematical software (cs.MS) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also addresses difficulties faced by students in learning and applying mathematics, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and education technology (cs.ET).
